&lt;p&gt;An exciting opportunity has arisen for an Senior PACS/RIS Administrator to join our PACS / RIS Team, an individual with a commitment to actively contribute to our busy team as well as being able to work autonomously.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Main duties will be to be assist in the administration of the Picture Archiving and Communication System(s) (PACS) and Radiology Information System (RIS) across site together with clinical imaging applications as required.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;You will also be required to work with the PACS/RIS Technical Manager promoting innovation, continuous service improvement and modernisation, and clinical excellence.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;You will have excellent technical and problem solving skills, with a ‘can do’ attitude.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Good knowledge and experience of diagnostic radiography is essential together with data analysing skills and a recognised IT qualification such as BTEC in Computer Studies, Microsoft Certificate Professional (MCP).&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;For further details / informal visits contact:&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Nigel Youell Radiology IM&amp;T Manager Email Nigel.Youell@nhs.net Telephone number07784 000321 (8am to 5pm Monday to Friday only)&lt;/p&gt;
